Review comment:
       I am not sure this is a way to do things in C++ part of Arrow. So I will add a note to clarify. `Dateutil` package currently does not have a method to extract POSIX name of the timezone. It is possible to use `_filename` but the output can be `'/usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Brussels'` or `'Europe/Brussels'` as in example:
   
   ```
   >>> import dateutil.tz
   >>> tz = dateutil.tz.gettz('Europe/Brussels')
   >>> tz
   tzfile('/usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Brussels')
   >>> tz._filename
   '/usr/share/zoneinfo/Europe/Brussels'
   ```
   see  https://github.com/dateutil/dateutil/issues/76#issuecomment-91226288.
   
   For this reason I am selecting a substring to get the name from the `tz._filename.` Please let me know if this is not a good way to go.




